Voluntas is a decentralized platform for patients to engage with clinical research. Clinical trial recruitment is a primary bottleneck behind delays in medical research, and despite biopharma companies spending a great deal (over $6.5k per recruited patient), 80% of trials are delayed due to recruitment issues. We’re combining a traditional business-to-business operation that sells data and services to industry with a tokenized model that rewards patients for contributing their data and engaging with the research ecosystem. Patients have clear control and ownership over their data and share in the economic value generated.
Voluntas is founded by entrepreneurs with experience co-founding successful companies (raised $100m+ venture, valued at over $1B) in the health data and clinical trials spaces, including TrialSpark and Canvas Medical. ValidLogo batch b1Altbasehttps://cryptojobslist.com/companies/altbasehttps://twitter.com/altbaseappNot found.https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_banners/1375938273374216192/1633048205/1500x500https://twitter.com/altbaseapphttps://twitter.com/altbaseapp/photohttps://twitter.com/altbaseapp/header_photoAltbasehttps://altbase.com/
Background About This Entire Project (Our story)
 
I am the CEO and Founder. I initially started this project as a crypto token in early 2021 fully bootstrapped and a one man army. I started livestreaming while building the project every single day for about 3-4 months (it was brutal, fun and also i didn't know what i was doing - but the idea kept evolving as I kept building the ecosystem).
 
Having a strong background in marketing and sales - I was able to attract lots of people to the community and to buying the token - we went from a $500,000 valuation to $88M valuation at the height of the crypto market (All in a span of 2-3 months)
 
We then sold some tokens in order to keep funding the project which then developed into an app. The reason why transitioned into an app was because I didn't just want to be a 'hype'/'meme' crypto project but rather a utility for the new crypto user of tomorrow. Crypto is growing day by day and there is a huge problem when it comes Onboarding into the crypto industry (getting cash into crypto, maneuvering around markets, which investments to pick, etc. etc.) - This is where Altbase App comes in.
 
I used the funds from the tokens sold to hire an app development company (because I had no idea how to build an app but I decided to take that risk) - I pushed that company to build the app in less than 2 months. During that time, I marketed the app like crazy and continued to livestream. I hired team members onboard to help me grow the community and oversea some of the app development and marketing. Our members were excited leading up to the app launch.
 
App launch came and within 1-2 weeks we had a flood of 15K-20K users. We had daily users and retention was great - however I knew that working with a 3rd part app dev company was unsustainable long-term because (too expensive, and I wanted people who believe in the vision LONGTERM) - Nonetheless, this was enough for a proof of concept. This took place around summer of 2021.
 
September - October 2021: We realized that we had to switch over to hiring our own developers because we want to build something long-term and sustainable and have developers that share the vision for the app. So we scrapped the entire app and rebuilt it from scratch which took us 3 months to build the Beta version (which is what we have now):
https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.altbase&hl=en_US&gl=US
 
We have active users - but the app isn't where we want it to be and feel development could move a faster if the right technical product manager was set in place.
 
I believe what we're building here will fulfill a huge need in the crypto space as there is lots of room to grow for any platform that builds in this industry.
 
The goal is 1M users and to help all those users go from "idk about crypto" to "Crypto is going to help me retire" - which will eventually result in Altbase hitting a $1B valuation.
 
I know I typed out a fairly long story but I just wanted to get this vision out.
If you believe you're perfect for this role and believe in what we're doing please do not hesitate to reach out and apply.
I look forward to speaking with you.
Please email us at Jobs@Altbase.com

ValidLogo batch b1Tiny Titanshttps://dappradar.com/dapp/tiny-titans
https://twitter.com/@RealTinyTitans
Not found.https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1653074947219111947/w-fSXdLJ_bigger.jpghttps://twitter.com/@RealTinyTitanshttps://twitter.com/@RealTinyTitans/photohttps://twitter.com/@RealTinyTitans/header_photoTiny Titanshttps://tinytitans.fi/
BATTLE OF THE TITANS
The Tiny Titans are NFTs which you can collect, trade and send forth into battle against each other - all happening decentral within the logic of the deployed smart contract. Each Tiny Titan starts off with level one at mintage but receives a random set of values for its attributes - making each Tiny Titan one hundred percent unique!
MINT YOUR TITAN
Everybody can mint a new Tiny Titan to a wallet - if this wallet does not own a Tiny Titan yet. All you need for minting a new Tiny Titan are 0.25 BNB.
On mint, each Tiny Titan starts off with level one, a random set of values for its attributes and an unique artwork representing it.
BATTLE AND LEVEL
To raise the level of your Tiny Titan you need to battle other Tiny Titans. It doesn’t matter if you win or lose, you will always get experience - you gain much more experience for winning tho. If you want to level your Tiny Titan fast you can increase your winning possibility by either fighting against specific Tiny Titans which attributes you looked up beforehand or by adding powerups to your Tiny Titan which boost its attributes for one battle before attacking others.
TRADE AND COLLECT
Every owner of a Tiny Titan has the possibility to sell his Tiny Titan. For this he sets a price for his collectible, which will add it to our list of Tiny Titans that are up for sale. The owner can still battle others while his Tiny Titan hasn’t been sold. And if he has a change of mind, the owner can always cancel the sell offer.

Using a novel address-based encryption algorithm, the Celo protocol makes sending money as easy as sending a text. Additionally, Celo uses stable-value tokens pegged to fiat currencies, like the US Dollar, to minimize volatility. Celo is an open protocol enabling many to participate in the system, even with a budget Android smartphone. The first application that launched on the Celo platform, Valora, is a social payments and money transfer app, aimed at developing markets.

This is the core software that validators on the Celo network run to peer with each other on a p2p network, reach consensus on new blocks, and create the fundamental platform upon which the Celo community builds user-facing applications. The Cosmic Landscape of CosmoDoodle
Theoretical physicist Leonard Susskind wrote a whole book dedicated to the so-called cosmic landscape, which is the space of the Super-Megaverse with many ‘pocket universes’, in which habitable zones, such as Earth, can be found.
The diversity of the cosmic landscape suggests very different living conditions. Some planets are too cold, if their orbits are far from the main star of the system. On others, it is too hot, if the distance to the star is minimal. Nevertheless, the point is that any environment can be home to a particular form of life. The inhabitants of the ‘steam room’ planet and the planet-ocean will not be alike – that's for sure. However, each population take the laws of physics on the home planet as familiar and normal as earthlings take the fact that they need air for living, and for comfortable living the temperature at the Earth's surface should be 15 degrees Celsius.
Today there is scientific evidence that the cosmic landscape design includes at least 10^500 habitable zones. This has worked out as inspiration for the galaxy of artists to create unique CosmoDoodle worlds. And you have got a chance to walk along them under the stars...

ValidLogo batch b1Filecoin Foundationhttps://cryptojobslist.com/companies/filecoin-foundation
https://twitter.com/FilFoundation
Not found.https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_banners/1302398882186366976/1682426591/1500x500https://twitter.com/FilFoundationhttps://twitter.com/FilFoundation/photohttps://twitter.com/FilFoundation/header_photoFilecoin Foundationhttps://fil.org/
The Filecoin Foundation (FF) is an independent organization that facilitates governance of the Filecoin network, funds critical development projects, supports the growth of the Filecoin ecosystem, and advocates for Filecoin and the decentralized web. In 2017, the creators of Filecoin envisioned that an independent Filecoin Foundation would serve as the long-term governance body for the Filecoin Ecosystem. They gave the Foundation the mandate to “grow an open ecosystem for decentralized storage” and to “give developers an open and sustainable platform to build, enhance and monetize those services.” They wanted the Foundation to be modeled on Foundations for other open source projects like the Apache Software Foundation, the Mozilla Foundation and the Linux Foundation. The Filecoin Foundation operates independently of Protocol Labs, the organization that designed and built the Filecoin network. As a member of our early-stage team, you will have the opportunity to help define our growth as the organization scales. This is a full-time position, remote from anywhere in the world.

Gameplay
Each car has 4 stats points: Speed, power, drift, fuel.
As a player in CryptoCars your mission is to win races (PvP, PvC racing) to get experience points and materials. To participate in a race, cars need fuel. Daily, fuel will be automatically refilled.
When you gain enough experience points, you can use materials to upgrade your car level. Materials & cars can be sold on Marketplace.
Play to Earn Model
New players need to buy a car on Marketplace to start playing game. When completing the mission, the player will receive materials to upgrade level or build a new car that can be sold for money.

Banksy Swap is a new DeFi Yield Farming project on Binance Smart Chain.
Token Info
Name: BANKSY TOKEN
Symbol: BANKSY
Chain: Binance Smart Chain #BSC
Contract: 0x957B82c9FF3E7D7d3B67A2Df9B84A200a7403ab1
 
How it works
Like most of the yield farming on DeFi is done via liquidity pools. A liquidity pool is a smart contract that holds on to and locks the cryptocurrencies/tokens of investors. Liquidity providers contribute to the liquidity of a trading pair pool, such as BANKSY-BNB, by depositing their crypto (in this case BANKSY and BNB) in the pool, receiving LP (Liquidity Pool) BANKSY tokens in return.
The assets in a liquidity pool create a market where the assets can be exchanged by traders. If there were no liquidity pool, it would not be possible for a trader to swap tokens, as there would be no “other side” of the trade. When an investor swaps tokens (e.g. BANKSY for BNB), he needs to pay a trading fee.
This fee is paid to the liquidity providers in proportion to the amount of liquidity (BANKSY and BNB) they have added to the pool. An investor who “owns” a big part of the liquidity pool will receive more trading fees compared to an investor that provided little liquidity to the pool. The fee at Pancakeswap is fixed at 0.17% per token swap trading.
Our team understand the triumph you feel when you find a good farm and the dejection of a rugpull. This farm is a collection of our team's view on what we think are the elements of a successful farm model. For this purpose, we decided on a low emission rate (0.5) to our platform. We believe this model will help end users earn maximum yields over an extended period of time.
Banksy Swap is a novel DeFi Yield Farming project hosted on the Binance Smart Chain. Through liquidity pools that facilitate yield farming, Banksy Swap manages a market for the BANKSY-BNB trading pair. Its distinctive appeal lies in its commitment to maintaining a low emission rate and providing a sustainable farming model that aims to maximize yields over an extended time.

Solana is a global state machine, and the world’s most performant blockchain. It gives developers the confidence to build for the long term by delivering predictable scaling without compromising security or composability. Solana’s performance is driven by a single global state, which is capable of processing tens of thousands of smart contracts at once, and by Proof of History, a distributed clock that unlocks low-latency, sub-second finality across the global state. What's so special about engineering at Multis?
Most people would call Multis "just an interface" but you'd probably call it a server-less, backend-less, password-less, real-time full stack Clojure Script static decentralized web application. As for our engineering principles, we only have one: simplicity.

ValidLogo batch b1Nomadic Labshttps://cryptojobslist.com/companies/nomadic-labs
https://twitter.com/labosnomades
https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_banners/1075428307997548545/1614697832/1500x500https://twitter.com/labosnomadeshttps://twitter.com/labosnomades/photohttps://twitter.com/labosnomades/header_photoNomadic Labshttps://nomadic-labs.com/
Nomadic Labs / Tezos protocol
Nomadic Labs est une société française de recherche et de développement dont la mission principale est de fournir une implémentation du protocole Tezos. L’entreprise comporte 35 employés, la plupart issus de la recherche française en informatique.
Tezos est une Blockchain créée en 2014, qui suite à une levée de fond de 232 millions de dollars, a mis en place une fondation de droit suisse (la fondation Tezos) dont la mission est d’appuyer le développement et l’adoption de cette nouvelle technologie de blockchain.
À ce titre, la fondation Tezos finance un écosystème assez décentralisé d’entreprises dans le monde, dont Nomadic Labs, pour mener à bien ce projet.
Nomadic Labs, dont la mission est aussi d’assurer l’adoption de la technologie Tezos en France, souhaite recruter une ou un développeur Blockchain Senior pour assurer une présence technique ainsi qu’un support auprès d’un écosystème d’entreprises qui graviteront autour de Nomadic Labs.
Cet écosystème sera composé des acteurs suivants :

ESN (Entreprises de Service du Numérique) : il s’agit des entreprises capables de développer des projets informatiques sur la technologie Blockchain (y compris les « smart contracts »).

STO platforms : Il s’agit des entreprises capables de « tokeniser » des actifs (financiers : comme des parts d’entreprises ou des obligations, ou encore immobiliers : comme des immeubles).

Grands comptes : Il s’agit des entreprises qui sont susceptibles d’adopter la technologie Tezos. Nomadic Labs et l’écosystème Tezos, a choisi de mettre l’accent en priorité sur le secteur financier, plus susceptible d’investir en ressources dans cette technologie avec notamment les banques, ou les assureurs.

En plus de l'accompagnement direct de cet écosystème d'entreprises proches, la mission inclura une partie de support technique à la communauté Tezos dans son ensemble, dans le but d'assurer succès et adoption.
Nomadic Labs is a French research and development company focused on implementing the Tezos protocol. They work in collaboration with the Tezos Foundation to support the development and adoption of this blockchain technology. Nomadic Labs aims to recruit a senior blockchain developer to provide technical support to an ecosystem of companies involved in Tezos adoption and to assist the broader Tezos community.

ValidLogo batch b1Norihttps://cryptojobslist.com/companies/norihttps://twitter.com/norihttps://pbs.twimg.com/profile_banners/928691337200676864/1658787018/1500x500https://twitter.com/norihttps://twitter.com/nori/photohttps://twitter.com/nori/header_photoNorihttps://nori.com/
Nori is a startup founded in October 2017 with the mission to enable global engagement to reverse climate change via carbon removal. By providing a marketplace where anyone in the world can pay for and get paid for removing and storing atmospheric carbon dioxide, Nori acts as a financial mechanism that will create new opportunities for climate innovation and carbon removal. 
We’re upgrading on the carbon offset space. Historically carbon offsets have been mired with opacity which then leads to a lack of confidence and trust in what projects are supported. Additionally, most carbon offsets (95%) represent paying someone to do less of a bad thing, i.e. mitigating emissions.
Nori is different in three key ways. First, Nori only supports carbon removal, or carbon sequestration, which is the only method that can actually reverse/negate carbon emissions. Second, Nori is the only platform with end-to-end marketplace of credits. Because we work directly with project owners who “supply carbon removal”, maintain the retirement of carbon removal credits, and track this all on the blockchain, Nori is providing a transparent and credible way to pay for carbon removal directly from project developers with no price markups. Lastly, with Nori’s API, businesses can offer environmental action and engagement directly to their customers at check-out or in-app, and immediately provide information on the project they supported, with immediate create of certificates with the customers name on it. 
We highly recommend that you review the information about Nori and its team before applying to this position at https://nori.com/careers.
Knowing us better will save you time, allowing you to assess whether or not we are a good fit for each other, and will also give you better context for completing the job application below.
Nori is a startup dedicated to reversing climate change through carbon removal. They operate a marketplace where individuals can pay for and get paid for removing and storing atmospheric carbon dioxide. Unlike traditional carbon offset mechanisms, Nori focuses solely on carbon removal, provides end-to-end marketplace transparency through blockchain technology, and offers businesses the ability to directly engage their customers in environmental action and awareness.
Nori is a startup founded in October 2017 with the mission to enable global engagement to reverse climate change via carbon removal. By providing a marketplace where anyone in the world can pay for and get paid for removing and storing atmospheric carbon dioxide, Nori acts as a financial mechanism that will create new opportunities for climate innovation and carbon removal. 
We’re upgrading on the carbon offset space. Historically carbon offsets have been mired with opacity which then leads to a lack of confidence and trust in what projects are supported. Additionally, most carbon offsets (95%) represent paying someone to do less of a bad thing, i.e. mitigating emissions.
Nori is different in three key ways. First, Nori only supports carbon removal, or carbon sequestration, which is the only method that can actually reverse/negate carbon emissions. Second, Nori is the only platform with end-to-end marketplace of credits. Because we work directly with project owners who “supply carbon removal”, maintain the retirement of carbon removal credits, and track this all on the blockchain, Nori is providing a transparent and credible way to pay for carbon removal directly from project developers with no price markups. Lastly, with Nori’s API, businesses can offer environmental action and engagement directly to their customers at check-out or in-app, and immediately provide information on the project they supported, with immediate create of certificates with the customers name on it. 
We highly recommend that you review the information about Nori and its team before applying to this position at https://nori.com/careers.
Knowing us better will save you time, allowing you to assess whether or not we are a good fit for each other, and will also give you better context for completing the job application below.Nori

https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_banners/1149448314158342144/1675438491/1500x500https://twitter.com/OasisProtocolhttps://twitter.com/OasisProtocol/photohttps://twitter.com/OasisProtocol/header_photoOasis Protocol Foundationhttps://oasisprotocol.org/
The Oasis Network is a Layer 1, proof-of-stake, decentralized network. It has two main components, the Consensus Layer and the ParaTime Layer.
The Consensus Layer is a scalable, high-throughput, secure, proof-of-stake consensus run by a decentralized set of validator nodes.
The ParaTime Layer hosts many parallel runtimes (ParaTimes), each representing a replicated compute environment with shared state.
Designed for the next generation of blockchain, the Oasis Network is the first privacy-enabled blockchain platform for open finance and a responsible data economy. Combined with its high throughput and secure architecture, the Oasis Network is able to power private, scalable DeFi, revolutionizing Open Finance and expanding it beyond traders and early adopters to a mass market. Its unique privacy features can not only redefine DeFi, but also create a new type of digital asset called Tokenized Data that can enable users to take control of the data they generate and earn rewards for staking it with applications — creating the first ever responsible data economy.

The Oasis Foundation was created to foster a global community around the Oasis ecosystem and support its growth and decentralization. At its core, the Oasis Foundation is a not-for-profit organization and is comprised of an international team with members in Europe, Asia and North America.

ValidLogo batch b1Obol Networkhttps://cryptojobslist.com/companies/obol-network
https://twitter.com/obolnetwork
https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_banners/1393178052809592832/1639404426/1500x500https://twitter.com/obolnetworkhttps://twitter.com/obolnetwork/photohttps://twitter.com/obolnetwork/header_photoObol Networkhttps://obol.tech/
Who Are We?
Obol is a remote first research and software development team focused on building decentralized software for public proof of stake blockchain networks. Over the past 12 months we have been building a community of strategic supporters across the entire stack to enable more resilient and distributed staking infrastructure on public blockchain networks through the Shared Secret Validator (SSV) effort, initiated by the Ethereum Foundation. 
SSV is a powerful infrastructure primitive that can be used in a variety of configurations and implemented on almost any public blockchain network. The primitive has been researched and designed to improve resiliency and security at the validator client and beacon node level of the Ethereum stack, mitigating risks such as crash faults, key theft, and slashing risk. This is achieved by splitting a validator key across multiple independently operating instances and utilizing threshold signatures to perform validation duties (think: a multi-sig validator). 
https://blog.obol.tech/lido-development-grant-to-obol/
Obol is currently focused on utilizing the SSV primitive as a building block to develop a trust-minimized staking protocol. We believe that this primitive is most useful at the lower layers of the blockchain stack and should be deployed to main net with an architecture that enables it to be built on top of, accelerating vertical innovation in staking products, similar to the way roll-up technologies have evolved over the past few years. 
Our mission is to increase the security and resiliency of public blockchain networks by evolving the SSV primitive to become a sustainable public good accessible by developers and validators all over the world.
The Obol protocol will become an open, community governed, self-sustaining project over the coming months and years. Its participants will be responsible for the security and distribution of consensus finding on the world's most used public blockchain networks. Together we will incentivize, buidl, and maintain distributed technology that makes public proof of stake networks a more secure and resilient foundation to build on top of.
Obol is a research and software development team dedicated to building decentralized software for public proof-of-stake blockchain networks, with a focus on developing a trust-minimized staking protocol.

Value is created and shared equitably by all stakeholders.
The ecosystem is owned by its users and used by its owners.

Opulous is a peer-to-peer decentralised finance platform that will provide loans to artists in the music industry without the need for traditional banking. Opulous will use blockchain technology to connect investors with artists needing a loan, driving fresh investment into an industry that is set to double revenues over the next decade.
Opulous raised $1.5 million in its seed round of funding. The platform will be developed on the Algorand blockchain; the Boston-based open-source software firm is also the lead investor. Associate investors are TrustVerse, Somesing, BASIC, Kosmos Capital and Opulous mother-company is Ditto Music.
Ditto Music is an award-winning global music distribution and record label services company, with experience processing more than $1 billion in royalties. It has supported more than 250,000 artists and labels worldwide, including Chance the Rapper, Ed Sheeran and Stormzy.
Join and help us revolutionise the cryptocurrency space and the music business industry!

$PAC is a digital asset based off of DASH with a solid foundation and a bright future. $PAC is a unique hybrid that combines a master node network at its foundation complimented with a vibrant community. These two networks synergize together and provide a strong foundation for $PAC’s future projects. The masternode network providers will engage the $PAC community to help steer 20% of the future coin supply on use cases focused on charity, content and alternative choices. We have just finished a successful redemption program with over 60,000 transactions where there were over three trillion old PAC, to the new coins called $PAC!
The PAC to $PAC redemption window will be officially closing on June 30th, 2018, but we will keep a small pool of coins available to uphold our originally published schedule. Currently, there are approximately ~300 million $PAC available to be used to help fuel the core operations and provide an incentive structure for the future management team of $PAC. $PAC has a DAO system like DASH, but this system lacks the efficiency and transparency that a traditional operational budget needs to succeed and minimize wasteful expenses etc. For example, as the price fluctuates projects submitted to the existing DAO system become massively overpaid or underfunded. Early on the founding team identified these issues and decided to build an operational budget and incentive program from the remaining $PAC. This pool of $PAC will be released into circulation with the commencement of this budget and the treasury position.
Finding the balance of decentralized system that competes in the digital asset space against centralized teams and operational personnel provides $PAC with significant challenges. We believe we have designed an excellent compromise that will make our community members and masternode holders satisfied. We actively invite applicants to apply for this role and help us succeed in achieving these goals.
As our operations expand, we need our management team to grow so we can continue to deliver excellence across a harmonized business front. $PAC currently has a presence all across the world and it is currently ranked around 250 as a digital asset. Join our team and help us deliver an outstanding, customer-oriented and community focused treasury management service.
